OL,6,FThe court heard she accused her
OL,7,Fhusband of hitting her with a shovel;
OL,8,Fpuncturing her car tyres; stealing her
OL,9,Ftax disc; throwing a statue through a
OL,10,Fglass door; urinating into a drawer
OL,11,Fand injuring her son with an ashtray.
OL,13,FIan Rawle, while on the phone to the
OL,14,Fpolice, said his wife stabbed him in
OL,15,Fthe chest and neck; placed a hosepipe
OL,16,Fthrough her sunroof and filled the car
OL,17,Fwith water; broke into his house and
OL,18,Fstole personal items; and hit him with
OL,19,Fa riding crop.
