OL,6,FChristine Rawle's son, Tom Rawle, told
OL,7,Fthe court he frequently witnessed his
OL,8,Fstep-father being violent, and was
OL,9,Fonce left with a 'severe burn' after
OL,10,Fhaving a hot ashtray thrown at him.
OL,12,FTom, 38, said he remembers Ian Rawle -
OL,13,Fwhom he referred to as 'dad' -
OL,14,Fstamping on his toys, punching and
OL,15,Fkicking his mother, insulting family
OL,16,Fmembers and having regular arguments.
OL,18,FOn one occasion, when he was about ten
OL,19,Fyears old, Tom said he was injured by
OL,20,FIan Rawle.
