OL,6,F"Dad and I were doing some homework,
OL,7,Fmaths I believe," Tom said.
OL,9,F"He was becoming progressively
OL,10,Ffrustrated as he was giving me tasks
OL,11,Fwhich were beyond what I was able to
OL,12,Fachieve.
OL,14,F"He got a metal ruler and hit me
OL,15,Faround the head with it. It was
OL,16,Fpainful and unjustified."
OL,18,FTom Rawle told the court Ian Rawle
OL,19,Fthen picked up a hot ashtray and threw
OL,20,Fit at him.
